HEADWORD: Wingy
<hw>Wing"y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having wings;
rapid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>wingy</qex> speed outstrip the eastern wind.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Soaring with wings, or as if with wings; volatile
airy.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those <qex>wingy</qex> mysteries in divinity.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1657 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wink</ent>⟦br⟧
